description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the patient experience team. The Patient Experience Team is a Trust-wide support service which manages and co-ordinates the feedback the Trust receives about the services we provide from patients, their families and carers. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This information supports us to learn from patients’ experiences and review our services to ensure high standards of care are provided and improved outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to appoint a highly motivated individual who has recent and relevant knowledge of complaints handling and experience of managing difficult situations. The successful applicant will be an excellent communicator, have exceptional customer service skills, be a team player and be flexible in order to support the diverse and dynamic work load of the Patient Experience Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, they will be required to work with a wide range of colleagues within the Trust, to liaise with external stakeholders, and have good organisational awareness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is for 28 Hours per week based at North Devon District Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
